  "example": {
    "code": "Manually adding two vectors, using broadcasting:\n\n>>> import numpy as np\n>>> x = np.array([[1], [2], [3]])\n>>> y = np.array([4, 5, 6])\n>>> b = np.broadcast(x, y)\n\n>>> out = np.empty(b.shape)\n>>> out.flat = [u+v for (u,v) in b]\n>>> out\narray([[5.,  6.,  7.],\n       [6.,  7.,  8.],\n       [7.,  8.,  9.]])\n\nCompare against built-in broadcasting:\n\n>>> x + y\narray([[5, 6, 7],\n       [6, 7, 8],\n       [7, 8, 9]])",
    "output": "",
    "source": "derived"
  },
